Kernel Routine
==============

I do this everyday to stay up to date with kernel changes and learn
new things.


Morning routine
---------------

- Read latest RSS feeds (phoronix, LWN, lots of blogs from kernel
  devs...)
- Inspect latest patches from the subsystems I follow:

    Setup:
    git clone https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/next/linux-next.git
    git remote add netdev https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/netdev/net-next.git
    git remote add bpf https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/bpf/bpf-next.git
  
    cd linux-next
    git fetch origin && git fetch netdev && git fetch bpf
    # Netdev changes
    # use "log -p" to see the full patch 
    git log netdev/main -- drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ net/core/ include/linux/netdevice.h
    # bpf changes
    git log bpf/master -- kernel/bpf/ net/core/filter.c

- Skim over eBPF and mm mailing lists (I focus on RFCs and PATCH 0/X).


Night routine
-------------

Work on the project I am currently working on (a driver, my OS,
learning a tool like yocto, write a compiler....).